              "docstring": "Attach an evidence link to a hypothesis and recompute its confidence.\n\nArgs:\n    hypothesis_id: Hypothesis the evidence bears on.\n    evidence_id: Identifier of the evidence artifact.\n    stance: One of ``\"supports\"``, ``\"contradicts\"``, or ``\"context\"``.\n    weight: Evidence weight in the closed interval ``[0, 1]``.\n    evidence_kind: Category of evidence, used by the acceptance gate.\n    independence_group: Group used to collapse correlated evidence during scoring.\n    artifact_sha256: Optional SHA-256 of the backing artifact.\n    details: Optional structured details stored as JSON.\n    actor: Identity recorded in the audit log.\n\nReturns:\n    A dictionary with the new ``link_id`` and the recomputed ``confidence``.\n\nRaises:\n    ContractError: If the stance is invalid or the weight is outside ``[0, 1]``.\n    KeyError: If the hypothesis does not exist.",
