              "docstring": "Recompute a hypothesis confidence from its evidence using a bounded score.\n\nSupporting and contradicting weights are collapsed per independence group (taking the\nmaximum within each group) so correlated reports cannot inflate confidence by\nduplication, then combined with a neutral prior into a score in ``(0, 1)``.\n\nArgs:\n    connection: Open database connection to query.\n    hypothesis_id: Hypothesis whose evidence is scored.\n\nReturns:\n    The confidence rounded to six decimal places and clamped away from 0 and 1.",
